headlines.description: Japhet Kadji and Femi Olujobi turned in double-doubles and North Carolina A&T defeated Tennessee Tech 64-54 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kadji, Olujobi have double-doubles in 64-54 win

headlines.description: Chris Galbreath Jr. scored 22 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Sam Houston State survived late turnovers to edge Little Rock 57-55 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Galbreath scores 22, Sam Houston State hangs on to win 57-55

headlines.description: Dedric Boyd hit four 3-pointers and scored 19 and DeAndre Dishman scored six in a 10-0 run to end the game as Eastern Kentucky rallied past Charleston Southern 70-65 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late run lifts E Kentucky over Charleston Southern 70-65

headlines.description: Tyler Bey scored eight of his 12 points in the second overtime period, including all four of his free throws, and Colorado overcame a 37-point performance by Mike Daum to beat South Dakota State 112-103 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado overcomes Daum, South Dakota State 112-103 in 2OT

headlines.description: Marcus Foster hit three 3-pointers and scored 15 to lead five players in double figures and Creighton rolled to an 87-36 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Friday night.
Demetrius Denzel-Dyson scored 15 of his 17 points in the first half when Samford took a 25-point lead on its way to a 98-51 victory over Thomas University on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 5 Samford players in double figures in 98-51 victory

headlines.description: Joseph Kilgore totaled 11 points, seven rebounds and four steals and Perry Francois scored a career-high 11 points off the bench to propel Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 71-55 win over Division II member St. Mary's (Texas) on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M-CC turns back D-II St. Mary's (Texas) 71-55

headlines.description: Dikembe Dixson scored 19, Dominique Matthews added 18 and Illinois-Chicago led the entire second half in a 76-60 win over Dartmouth on Friday night.
Reid Travis and Daejon Davis each scored 20 points and Stanford beat Denver 75-62 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Travis, Davis each score 20 in Stanford's win over Denver

headlines.description: Frankie Ferrari came off the bench to score a career-high 19 points and added five assists and Chase Foster knocked down 4 of 5 from 3-point range and scored 17 to power San Francisco to a 74-61 win over UC Davis on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ferrari, Foster lead San Francisco past UC Davis 74-61

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
